entries.title: Italian film legend Gina Lollobrigida dies at age 95
entries.description: Italian film legend Gina Lollobrigida, who achieved international stardom during the 1950s and was dubbed “the most beautiful woman in the world," has died.

entries.title: London police officer admits to raping and sexually assaulting a dozen women over nearly 2 decades
entries.description: Metropolitan Police officer David Carrick has admitted raping and sexually assaulting a dozen women over nearly two decades.

entries.title: Video shows final moments before deadly Nepal plane crash
entries.description: Video has emerged of the plane that crashed in Nepal over the weekend, killing at least 69 people.

entries.title: Ukraine prepares for new offensive as Russia and Belarus begin joint drills
entries.description: Ukraine is preparing for battle in this quiet forest clearing less than five minutes driving from the border with Russia's close ally, Belarus.

entries.title: At least 68 killed in Nepal plane crash
entries.description: At least 68 people were killed after a passenger plane crashed moments before it was scheduled to land in Nepal. NBC News’ Molly Hunter reports.

entries.title: Death toll in Russian strike on Ukrainian building rises to 40
entries.description: The death toll from a Russian missile strike on an apartment building in the southeastern Ukrainian city of Dnipro has risen to 40, authorities said Monday.

entries.title: Italian Mafia leader arrested after 30 years on the run
entries.description: Italy's most-wanted man, mafia boss Matteo Messina Denaro, was arrested Monday after three decades on the run. He was apprehended in the Sicilian capital, Palermo, Italy's Carabinieri police division said.

entries.title: Italy's most wanted Mafia boss arrested after 30 years on the run
entries.description: Italy's most-wanted man, mafia boss Matteo Messina Denaro, was arrested in Sicily on Monday after 30 years on the run, police said.

entries.title: Search resumes for four people missing in Nepal after deadly air crash
entries.description: Rescuers resumed searching on Monday in Nepal for four people still missing after the Himalayan nation’s deadliest plane crash in 30 years, officials said.

entries.title: American imprisoned in Iran launches hunger strike, says he was 'left behind' in 2016 U.S-Iran prisoner swap
entries.description: Siamak Namazi, an American imprisoned in Iran, announced a hunger strike to mark seven years since he was “unconscionably” left out of a 2016 prisoner swap.

entries.title: Former Afghan female lawmaker and guard are shot dead at home, police say
entries.description: Former Afghan female lawmaker Mursal Nabizada and her bodyguard have been shot dead by unknown assailants at her home in the capital, Kabul, police said.
